adrFormatAddress: 184 9th Ave, New York, NY 10011, USA

editorialSummary.text: Popular bakery in a quaint space whipping up cakes & cupcakes, plus pies & cheesecakes.

originalText.text:
I’ve been going to Billy’s on 9th ave since they opened. Got many a birthday cake there.  The banana cake was the best, dense and moist.  Last time i went they sold me the last piece and it was dry and hard, so disappointed.  I decided to try again today and got a slice from a nearly full cake. The cake seemed kind of short and then when i got it, it felt very light. When i opened it later i realized there was an entire layer off the cake they used to serve. You’d think a small business would have more respect to their customers than to cheat them out of a layer.
See ya Billy, not going back

originalText.text:
I’m sorry but I must say this use to be “THE PLACE” for amazing portions of carrot cake in NYC but I guess the price of ingredients has gotten extremely high and now portion size must decrease as well. You may save .95 but does that really help when your customer base is no longer satisfied with the product?

Judging by the comments it might be time to rethink this strategy. It was very disappointing to see the cakes so tiny in the shop! At least the staff was kind but obviously equally embarrassed about the size of the cakes too. I am sure they get a lot of comments and complaints daily about it.
So I refused to make a big deal to the staff. They are just doing what management now requires of them I’m sure.

I went in to get a 2 slices for my husband and me as a celebratory dessert for his birthday. It’s been a tradition to get Billy’s carrot cake for special occasions. But when I saw the size of the cakes this time around I couldn’t believe it! It really feels as if one is being slighted out of what use to be something so memorable and enjoyable.
It’s hard to enjoy it now.

originalText.text: Absolutely love how this place is put together. This is a sit down spot for the lucky couple groups that get to come in first. In our experience, it wasn’t really packed but wouldn’t be surprised if this place had a line every now and then. They have these little cups with smashed cupcakes and the banana pudding is stupid delicious. The whole ambiance is really nice. Keep up the good work!

originalText.text: Shrinkflation warning. The $7 cake slices used to be three layers, then went to two layers, and now are pretty much a squashed cake. Frankly, I wish they would have kept the 3 layers and raised the price. Think the baker has lost their pride. It feels sad in here compared to the past. Kudos to the counter employers who are usually warm/welcoming.

originalText.text:
I LIKE BILLYS, I HAVE NOT HAD EVERYTHING TO GIVE  A BIG OVERALL REVIEW,BUT  I HAD A COUPLE OF CUPCAKES, AND I HAD THE CARROT CAKE WHICH I BELIEVE IS A POPULAR ITEM THERE, ..... THE FROSTING WAS A BIT THICK AND SWEET....THE CAKE ITSELF WAS GREAT, YOU CAN SEE AND TASTE THE CARROTS, THE WALNUTS ,THE RAISINS ... THE TEXTURE OF THE CAKE WAS COMPLETELY MOIST, FLUFFY ... DELIGHTFUL....
LOCATED IN THE CHELSEA AREA  9TH AVE NOT TO FAR FROM THE C,AND E TRAIN WHICH IS LOCATED ON 8TH AVE 23RD STREET...
THERE ARE A LOT OF RESTAURANTS IN THE AREA ALL WALKING DISTANCE, MOST EATERIES ARE  DIRECTLY ON 23RD STREET HEADING TOWARDS  1ST  AVE COMING FROM 8TH AVE , THE HIGH LINE IS ONE BLOCK AWAY, BETWEEN 9TH AND  10TH AVE DEPENDING ON WHAT STREET YOU ARE COMING FROM...
THERE ARE NOT TO MANY BAKERIES IN MANHATTAN, BILLY'S HAS A VERY VERY SMALL LIMIT OF VEGAN PASTRIES, THEY ARE BUILDING UP THERE VEGAN MENU ACCORDING TO  BAKER....
BILLY'S IS AN OLD TIME NOSTALGIC FEELING WE ALL MISS, YOU GET THIS FEELING AS SOON AS YOU WALK IN I LOVE IT, THE WAITERS ARE NICE, CUSTOMERS EXTREMELY POLITE , I WOULD DEFINITELY RECOMMEND COMING IN, VERY WELL KEPT IT WAS SUPER CLEAN, IM A STICKLER FOR CLEANLINESS..
SO STOP BY IF YOU EVER GET A CHANCE AN TRY THE CARROT CAKE AND  SEE FOR YOURSELF...
